Reasoning: The paper deals with lower bounds for normed Basic Process Algebra (BPA), which is a formal language used to model concurrent systems. The paper uses techniques from logic and automata theory to prove the lower bounds. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with regularity problems, which are related to formal language theory, so cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with complexity theory, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LT (Theoretical Computer Science) as possible sub-categories.
